cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.DL, cs.CY 

The paper focuses on keyphrase indexing, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of text denoising is a natural language processing technique, which falls under the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning models (cs.LG) and deep learning (cs.DL) for training the keyphrase indexer. Finally, the three domains used for experimentation (food and agriculture, high energy physics, and biomedical science) suggest a possible connection to cybernetics (cs.CY).
